            <summary>
              <p>François Déroche schreibt zum Fragment KFQ31 (Déroche,  <ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/QJQEKNSJ" sameAs="QJQEKNSJ" type="zotero">The Abbasid Tradition, London 1992</ref>, S. 82): "31 / Single folio / Mid-9th century AD / Fragmentary (largest dimensions now 9.5x16cm), with 8 lines to the page / <hi rend="italic">Material</hi> Parchment; the recto is the hair side / <hi rend="italic">Text area</hi> 6.4x12.5cm / Script Related to style D.III / <hi rend="italic">Accession no</hi>. KFQ31 / The text is <hi rend="italic">Sūrat al-aḥzāb</hi> (XXXIII), verses 64-69. It is written in brown ink. The diacritical dots have been added. Red dots indicate the vocalization. Individual verses are unpunctuated, but the end of every fifth verse is marked by a gold Kufic <hi rend="italic">hāʾ</hi>. The lower part of the folio has been severely damaged.”</p>
            </summary>
